title: Gonadotropins for ovulation induction in women with polycystic ovary syndrome.
abstract: Ovulation induction with follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) is a second-line treatment in women with polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) who do not ovulate or conceive on clomiphene citrate or letrozole, though induction protocols and types of gonadotropins used vary greatly.
journal: The Cochrane database of systematic reviews
